The non-governmental organisation says the family has been under severe stress, worried about their future and where they&#8217;ll live. JOHANNESBURG - Gift of the Givers says it will continue housing the Chauke family until they have a place to stay after their home was washed away and their daughter Everlate killed in flash floods.The non-governmental organisation says the family has been under severe stress, worried about their future and where they ll live.Their daughter, also known as Everlyn, was ripped from her father's grip during heavy rains in Gauteng last month. On Wednesday, family and community members gathered as the three-year-old girl was laid to rest.The toddler s body was found along the banks of the Jukskei River in Buccleuch.WATCH: Evelyn Chauke laid to rest(Edited by Shimoney Regter)